RACE.RACE_TEXT: AQUEDUCT RACE 1 1M Dirt CR: 63. Maiden Claiming Purse 35000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD FOALED IN NEW YORK STATE AND APPROVED BY THE NEW YORK STATE-BRED REGISTRY. Weight, 122 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000 (1.5% Aftercare Assessment Due At Time Of Claim Otherwise Claim Will Be Void).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TONIGHT WE LOVE disputed the pace on the inside of a foe, shook clear in the two path midway through the turn, extended the advantage into upper stretch, drew off under the crop into the final furlong and widened while kept to the task. FROSTY INVASION settled off the pace, was urged along passing the nine-sixteenths, moved from the rail to the two path while hard ridden around the turn, came out into upper stretch and safely secured the place while no match for the winner. TREAT STREET was bumped in the hindquarters at the start, settled off the pace, moved out near the five-eighths pole, was urged four wide around the turn, came out into upper stretch, dropped back while remaining on her inside lead and weakened but was well clear for the show. MENILY contested the pace on the outside, vied in the three path on the turn, dropped back outside the five-sixteenths, took a very awkward stride while out of contention outside the furlong marker and faltered. VIRTUAL BEAUTY pressed the early pace between horses, dropped back with five furlongs to run, fell further back leaving the backstretch, rounded the turn in the two path and also faltered. HAIL BRITANNIA was hard to load then fractious in the gate, broke in and bumped the hindquarters of a foe then was taken up severely, spotted the front many lengths, angled in at the rear, tossed her head entering the main-track, lagged at the back, went three wide around the turn and trailed.

ENTRY.NAME: Tonight We Love
ENTRY.COMMENT: pace inside foe,shook clear 2path 3/8,drew off,kept to task

ENTRY.NAME: Frosty Invasion
ENTRY.OWNER: Rosenthal Robert D Greenberg Martin and Rosenthal Peter

ENTRY.NAME: Hail Britannia
ENTRY.COMMENT: hard to load,fractious gate,broke in,bmpd,tkn up badly,trailed

RACE.RACE_TEXT: AQUEDUCT RACE 2 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 97. Claiming Purse 55000. (UP TO $9,570 NYSBFOA) FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since August 1 Allowed 3 lbs. Claiming Price $32,000 (Maiden And Claiming Races For $25,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances) (1.5% Aftercare Assessment Due A t Time Of Claim Otherwise Claim Will Be Void).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PRISONER went to the front then showed the way with a clear advantage, extended the lead along the rail on the turn, remained well clear under a drive into the final furlong and maintained a safe advantage under strong urging. THINKABOUTIT settled on the outside, was urged four wide on the turn, turned into upper stretch under a drive, gained on the winner in the final furlong and finished willingly to just get the place. JEMOGRAPHY settled at the rear of the field, saved ground on the turn, turned into the stretch in the two path, gained with good energy in the final furlong and finished well to just miss the place while narrowly up for the show. NUCLEAR OPTION chased the pace on the outside then in the three path around the turn, kept on well in pursuit of the winner in the final furlong and finished willingly to just miss the trifecta. ALCOOLS was hustled from the gate, chased the pace down the backstretch, dropped back near the seven-sixteenths, fell further back while two then three wide on the turn and weakened. LAFITTE'S FLEET settled towards the rear, moved from the two path to the four path around the turn and failed to threaten.

ENTRY.NAME: Jemography
ENTRY.OWNER: Epona Racing Stable Jasinski Clyde X and Toga Party Racing Stable
ENTRY.COMMENT: settled at rear, inside turn, 2path into lane, willingly, up show

ENTRY.NAME: Prisoner
ENTRY.OWNER: Baker, Charlton and Paolangeli, Francis J.
ENTRY.COMMENT: clear pace,extended lead rail turn,held,strong urging

RACE.RACE_TEXT: AQUEDUCT RACE 3 6F Dirt CR: 72. Maiden Claiming Purse 35000. FOR MAIDENS, FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD FOALED IN NEW YORK STATE AND APPROVED BY THE NEW YORK STATE-BRED REGISTRY. Weight, 122 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000 (1.5% Aftercare Assessment Due At Time Of Claim Otherwise Claim Will Be Void).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TREVOR BARDETTE bobbled at the start but broke in front, showed the way down the backstretch, extended the advantage while inside around the turn, drew off under a drive into the final furlong and proved much the best. REUNION TOUR settled on the outside, was urged four wide around the turn and safely secured the place while no match for the winner. THE GREAT GAZOO was coaxed along just off the pace on the outside, chased four then three wide around the turn and weakened while clear for the show. NOAH'S DESTINY chased the pace down the backstretch, dropped from the three path to the rail around the turn and tired. MR. BUSTA settled off the pace, steadied while in tight along the rail early on the turn then dropped back and capitulated. IRON HORIZON chased the pace down the backstretch, dropped back two then three wide on the turn and retreated. TYRANNOSAURUS REX broke in and hit the gate, moved out while urged along at the rear, went three then four wide on the turn and failed to respond.

ENTRY.COMMENT: broke in,hit gate,hustled,moved out,3-4w turn,no response

ENTRY.COMMENT: settled, steadied along rail 7/16, dropped back, empty

ENTRY.NAME: Iron Horizon
ENTRY.OWNER: McMahon Joseph G McMahon Anne Windswept Stables Bove John M Bove John V Bove Mic

ENTRY.NAME: The Great Gazoo
ENTRY.COMMENT: coaxed just off pace,outside,chased 4-3path turn,tired,clear show

ENTRY.NAME: Reunion Tour
ENTRY.OWNER: Ferraro James W Barbati Kenneth B and Citarella Diana

RACE.RACE_TEXT: AQUEDUCT RACE 4 7F Dirt CR: 79. Claiming Purse 28000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES FOUR YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since August 1 Allowed 3 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000 (Maiden And Claiming Races For $8,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances) (1.5% Aftercare Assessment Due At Tim e Of Claim Otherwise Claim Will Be Void).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GREATEST LOVE was hustled from the gate, contested the pace on the inside of the runner-up, vied inside to the two path on the turn, responded well when set down into upper stretch, shook off the runner-up inside the furlong marker and drew away under strong urging. ICY REPLY broke in and bumped soundly with a rival, disputed the pace on the outside, vied in the two to three path around the turn, was asked near the quarter-pole, battled outside the winner under a drive into the final furlong and proved no match while clear for the place. TILSA bumped solidly with a rival outside the three-quarter pole and steadied, was well placed behind the leading duo, dropped back under urging while inside to the two path around the turn, spun three wide into the stretch and weakened but was well clear for the show. PRAIRIE FIRE was coaxed along on the outside, went four wide under urging around the turn and came up empty. VIRADIA was last to commence, climbed some at the rear early, settled on the outside, went five wide under urging on the turn and was no factor. EXFILTRATION was bumped soundly at the start, bumped solidly with another foe early, dropped to the rear, saved ground on the turn and failed to respond.

ENTRY.NAME: Greatest Love
ENTRY.COMMENT: hustled,pace inside foe,ins-2path turn,shook clear ins1/8,drw off

ENTRY.COMMENT: bmpd hard brk,bmpd early,drop back,ins turn,no response

ENTRY.NAME: Icy Reply
ENTRY.COMMENT: brk in,bmpd soundly,outside pace,2-3p turn,ask1/4,no match

ENTRY.NAME: Viradia
ENTRY.COMMENT: last away,climbed some early,5wide turn,no factor

RACE.RACE_TEXT: AQUEDUCT RACE 5 7F Dirt CR: 65. Maiden Claiming Purse 43000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD FOALED IN NEW YORK STATE AND APPROVED BY THE NEW YORK STATE-BRED REGISTRY. Weight, 120 lbs. Claiming Price $40,000 (1.5% Aftercare Assessment Due At Time Of Claim Otherwise Claim Will Be Void).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: JOEYBIGNOSE broke in then dropped well off the pace, saved ground around the turn, swung six wide while rallying into upper stretch, closed fast to get the lead just inside the furlong marker then powered away while much the best. UKRAINIAN PRINCESS brushed with a foe leaving the chute, raced up close to the pace, chased four wide around the turn, was driven five wide into the stretch, remained on her inside until just outside the furlong marker then swapped to the proper lead and safely secured the place while no match for the winner. LADY BANKER went to the front, raced under extra left-rein pressure leaving the chute, showed the way down the backstretch under pressure from her outside, vied inside of a foe while along the rail on the turn, turned into upper stretch under a drive, battled into the final furlong and weakened while best of the rest. BERNING HONOR pressed the pace on the outside, vied in the two to three path around the turn, battled under a drive into the final furlong and tired. APEROL SPRITZ broke out then was quickly corrected by the rider, tracked the pace on the outside, dropped back under urging near the five-eighths, moved from the five path to the three path on the turn and captitulated. FORALLTHEGIRLS was last to begin, raced at the rear, went two to three wide on the turn and was no factor. REIGN OF THUNDER was hustled from the gate, brushed with an opponent leaving the chute, chased under strong urging, dropped back near the five-eighths, fell to the rear in the four to five path around the turn and faltered then was distanced.

ENTRY.NAME: Joeybignose
ENTRY.OWNER: The Four Horsemen Racing Stable Inc and Rahal Robert F
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke in,well off pace,ins turn,swung 6w1/4,rallied,going away

RACE.RACE_TEXT: AQUEDUCT RACE 6 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 81. Claiming Purse 28000. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since August 1 Allowed 3 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000 (Maiden And Claiming Races For $8,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances) (1.5% Aftercare Assessment Due At Time Of Claim Otherwis e Claim Will Be Void).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PRINCE JAMES was allowed to settle off the pace, saved ground while roused on the turn, rallied inside under the crop in the final furlong and closed well to get up at the wire. WINNING DRIVE bumped with a rival at the start, moved out while settling off the pace, was urged three then four wide around the turn, rallied five wide into upper stretch, closed well to get the lead into the final sixteenth, led until the final stride but was denied while able to get the place. MARVIN tracked the pace down the backstretch, issued an outside challenge in the three path around the turn, gained the advantage outside the quarter-pole, led under a drive while still on his inside lead into the final furlong, was headed by the runner-up at the sixteenth-pole and was outfinished while able to get the show. CHARLIE FIVE O moved in while going to the front, showed the way down the backstretch, was asked under threat while inside on the turn, lost the advantage outside the quarter-pole, came off the rail into upper stretch, fought on under a drive into the final sixteenth then weakened. FOREVER WICKED bumped with a rival at the start then was hustled, moved out early then angled in around the five-eighths, saved ground around the turn and gained ground but was no factor. CASALSA chased the pace down the backstretch, went four wide around the turn, pursued the leaders in the drive and lacked the needed kick. STANDUP was bumped on both sides at the start then moved out while sent hard, went three to four wide on the turn, came six wide into upper stretch and failed to threaten.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: AQUEDUCT RACE 7 1M Dirt CR: 91. Claiming Purse 39000. FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since August 1 Allowed 3 lbs. Claiming Price $16,000 (Maiden And Claiming Races For $12,500 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances) (1.5% Aftercare Assessment Due At Tim e Of Claim Otherwise Claim Will Be Void).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DADDY KNOWS showed the way on the outside, vied in the three path around the turn, moved clear late on that bend, responded well when asked for his best in upper stretch, drew off under a right-handed crop into the final furlong, lugged out after swapping back to his inside lead at the sixteenth-pole and proved much the best while held together to the wire. MY FRIENDS BEER settled off the pace, was urged three then two wide around the turn, turned into upper stretch under a drive and earned the place while no match for the winner. COOL QUARTET bumped with a rival at the start, was well placed down the backstretch, moved from the two path to the four path around the turn, turned into upper stretch in the three path and lacked the needed kick while able to get the show. VINTAGE HOLLYWOOD settled on the outside, angled in late on the backstretch, saved ground on the turn, spun three wide into the stretch and failed to rally. TRUCULENT was coaxed from the gate, attended the pace down the backstretch, vied along the rail on the turn, dropped back late on that bend and tired. CRYPTO CASH was hustled from the gate then settled off the pace, was urged along in the two path around the turn, came four wide into the stretch and failed to threaten. MICROSCOPE bumped with a rival at the start, settled at the rear, went three wide on the turn, came five wide into the stretch and was no factor.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: AQUEDUCT RACE 8 1 1/4M Dirt CR: 92. Allowance Purse 82000. (UP TO $14,268 NYSBFOA) FOR FOUR YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON $18,000 OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER OR STATE BRED ALLOWANCE OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Other Than Claiming Or Starter At A M ile Or Over Allowed 3 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GOOD SKATE showed good speed from the outside, angled in while going to the front, raced inside around the first turn, showed the way down the backstretch, controlled the action while inside on the far turn, responded well when asked near the quarter-pole then came under a drive in upper stretch and proved much the best under strong urging. CURBSTONE was fractious in the gate, traveled around the first turn in the two path under restraint, moved up between foes outside the five-eighths, was urged four wide around the far turn, pursued the winner in the stretch and finished willingly for the place. TIMBUKTU broke out then was corrected while hustled, showed speed inside of the winner then conceded the front and was taken back and switched out, raced in the three path around the opening bend, stalked the pace on the outside, chased two to three wide around the far turn and weakened but earned the show. MAILMAN'S A FLYER broke out then was quickly corrected by the rider, settled on the inside, was urged along midway down the backstretch, saved ground on the far turn, moved out in upper stretch and failed to respond. BOLD VICTORY went four wide on the first turn, settled on the outside, was urged along midway down the backstretch, rounded the far turn in the four path and also failed to respond. UNION LIGHTS went three wide around the first turn, settled off the pace, was urged along passing the five-eighths, dropped back while inside to the two path on the far turn and faltered.

ENTRY.NAME: Mailman's a Flyer
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke out,settled inside,mvd out 3/16,lacked needed response

RACE.FOOTNOTES: VICTORY MONEY displayed good speed, moved in near the five-eighths, set the pace under pressure, vied inside on the turn, shook clear into upper stretch, responded well under the crop in the final furlong and held under strong urging. WANNA WINNA bumped with a rival at the start, moved in while well back early on the backstretch, went three to four wide on the turn and finished with good energy to just get the place. LUCKY LUCKY LUKE bumped with a rival at the start, angled out at the rear then raced on the far outside, went five wide around the turn, came six wide into the stretch and finished willingly to just miss the place while clear for the show. MORETHANAFEELING stumbled at the start then bumped with a foe, raced just off the pace, steadied along the rail early on the turn, moved to the two path later on that bend and lacked the needed response. ENGINEER EMPIRE was forwardly placed on the outside, chased four then three wide around the turn and lacked the needed kick. DUDLEY DICKERSON raced well back in the field, went four wide on the turn, moved out in upper stretch and was no factor. GEM MINT TEN was well placed just off the pace, moved from the two path to the four path under urging on the turn, spun five wide into the stretch and came up empty. SCARAMANGA bumped with an opponent at the start, pressed the pace on the outside then in three path around the turn, dropped back into upper stretch and capitulated. VOLCKER RULES angled in while well off the pace early on the backstretch, went three to four wide on the turn and was no factor. AWESOME FORCE raced just off the early pace, dropped back with five furlongs to run, saved ground on the turn and retreated. IN MY SHADOW lacked early speed, saved ground on the turn, came out into upper stretch and showed little. AMMAN showed early speed then chased the pace, sustained an injury to his right foreleg near the five-eighths pole and was pulled up then vanned off. TUNNEL VISION stumbled severely at the start and unseated the rider.
